WEBVTT

00:01.152 --> 00:04.526
<i>Previously on Mars.</i>

00:04.561 --> 00:06.069
We had arrived,

00:06.104 --> 00:08.860
yet our journey was just beginning.

00:08.895 --> 00:11.860
With Ben gone, I took command.

00:11.895 --> 00:15.443
Mars fought us
every step of the way.

00:16.193 --> 00:18.319
They say science and faith don't mix.

00:18.354 --> 00:19.767
Open the door!

00:21.020 --> 00:24.152
If they fail, I don't care how
much you invested, we're out.

00:24.187 --> 00:26.943
But when everything
is telling you you already lost.

00:26.978 --> 00:30.069
If they fail, everyone's out.

00:30.516 --> 00:32.628
There's nothing
you can do but believe.

00:33.544 --> 00:35.655
We ignored this
horizontal entrance because

00:35.680 --> 00:37.777
it was clogged with breakdown debris.

00:37.812 --> 00:40.682
So we made one
more leap into the darkness.

00:41.401 --> 00:44.069
Easy, easy, easy.

00:44.330 --> 00:49.110
Hoping there was some light
at the bottom of the abyss.

00:49.145 --> 00:51.194
The idea that
one of the lava tubes could be

00:51.235 --> 00:55.568
connected to a
tectonic cave is brilliant.

00:56.176 --> 00:57.610
We're deploying the dome.

00:57.944 --> 01:00.610
The flag is planted.
It's official.

01:00.645 --> 01:03.150
Humankind has a home on Mars.

